National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan recently spoke with Ethiopian Deputy Prime Minister Demeke Mekonnen regarding the ongoing humanitarian and human rights crisis in the Tigray region. Sullivan expressed the Biden Administration's deep concern and discussed several critical steps to address the crisis, including increasing humanitarian access, putting an end to hostilities, withdrawing foreign troops, and conducting independent investigations into atrocities and human rights violations. They also emphasized the importance of peaceful dialogue among regional leaders, with the African Union's support, to resolve disputes related to the al-Fashaga border and the Grand Ethiopia Renaissance Dam. Sullivan emphasized the United States' readiness to assist Ethiopia in addressing the crisis based on their longstanding bilateral partnership and friendship.